{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"43":"General Behavior (Kitab Al-Adab)"},"section_detail":{"43":{"hadithnumber_first":4773,"hadithnumber_last":5274,"arabicnumber_first":4773,"arabicnumber_last":5274}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":4909,"arabicnumber":4909,"text":"Rapporté par Aisha (la mère des croyants) رضي الله عنها : Quelque chose lui a été volé et elle a commencé à maudire le voleur. Le Messager d’Allah ﷺ lui dit : « Ne diminue pas son péché. »","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Daif"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Daif"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Daif"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Daif"}],"reference":{"book":43,"hadith":137}}]}